		<small><a href="//slashdot.org/~sound%2Bvision/journal/" title="Thursday August 07, 2014 @07:15AM" class="user_journal_display">Journal</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64498551"><p>The parents have the urge to blame someone.</p><p>They can blame the shooter; he's already dead, that's not satisfying.</p><p>They blame the cops; but not much accountability or change was won there.</p><p>The governor's solution is "Umm... mental health", which everyone takes as a joke, because they know what kind of provision the state gives them for healthcare. (None.)</p><p>So they start casting the blame in ever more distant and futile directions.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64498551">
